### Complete API Test Flow
### Run these requests in order from top to bottom

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1

### 1. Health Check (verify server is running)
GET http://localhost:3000/health

###

### 2. Register a new user
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 3. Login with the registered user
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "demo@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### 4. Get current user info (uses token from login automatically)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

###

### 5. Search for products by keyword
POST {{baseUrl}}/search/keyword
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "keyword": "Play Station 4"
}

###

### 6. Search by URL
POST {{baseUrl}}/search/url
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "url": "https://www.jumia.com.ng/sony-playstation-4-fat-console-plus-extra-controller-and-12-games-installed-including-fc26-411309660.html"
}

###

### 7. Save a comparison (requires authentication)
# @name saveComparison
POST {{baseUrl}}/comparisons
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "comparisonData": {
    "products": [
      {
        "platform": "jumia",
        "name": "HP Laptop 15.6 Intel Core i3",
        "price": 250000,
        "currency": "NGN",
        "rating": 4.5,
        "reviewCount": 120,
        "url": "https://www.jumia.com.ng/product-url",
        "availability": true,
        "imageUrl": null
      }
    ],
    "bestValueIndex": 0,
    "searchQuery": "hp laptop",
    "timestamp": "2024-02-24T20:30:00.000Z"
  }
}

###

### 8. Get all saved comparisons
GET {{baseUrl}}/comparisons
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

###

### 9. Delete a comparison (replace 1 with actual ID from step 8)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/comparisons/1
Authorization: Bearer {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

###
